                <h1>Understanding Background Parenchymal Enhancement and Breast Cancer Risk</h1>
                <p>Background parenchymal enhancement (BPE) in breast tissue, observed during MRI, reflects the vascularity of breast tissue. Increased BPE levels have been linked to a heightened risk of developing breast cancer, serving as a potential indicator for individual risk assessment. Understanding BPE can guide tailored screening and intervention strategies.</p>
